SIMPLE: monomerous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monomerous
<hw>Mo*nom"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. single;
<grk>mo`nos</grk> alone + <?/ part.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Composed of solitary parts, as a flower with one sepal, one petal,
one stamen, and one pistil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having but one joint; -- said of
the foot of certain insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monometallic</ent>⟦br⟧
